   The USDA/1890 National Scholars Program
   [hm_carver.gif]

   The National Scholars Program is a major effort of the United States
   Department of Agriculture and the seventeen 1890 Historically Black
   Land-Grant Institutions, to award scholarships to students to attend
   one of the seventeen universities and study agriculture, food, or
   natural resource sciences.

   Application deadline: January 15 of each calendar year



